The kafka cluster has nodes called brokers which handle
1.Data storage
2.Data replication
3.Serve client request

Streams of events are categorized as topic.Kafka topic.Topics can be partitioned.Not associated with one node but number of nodes.
A topic contained multiple logs and the same topic is associated with number of partitions which reside in different computers.

         |---------------Topic1-----------[p1,p0,p4](partitions)
Kafka----|---------------Topic2----------[p2,p3]
         |----------------Topic3---------[p1,p2,p0]

if the message has key it helps in knowing which partition the message reside else the message is distributed among partition in round robin fashion.
Partitions allow events to be scaled horizontally.

Consumers can be organized into consumer groups.
Consumer in consumer group is tied to a partition.

In traditional message queue the retention period is not configurable,same is true for kafka.

